		<item>
			<title>2024 Law Firm Consumer Reports : REPORT SUMMARY</title>
			<description>&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://image.lawtimes.co.kr/images/198413.jpg" alt="198413.jpg" style="opacity: 0;" height="10px" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="text-align: right;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://ailinggo.ai/" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;img src="https://image.lawtimes.co.kr/images/lingo2.jpg" alt="lingo2.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Special Reporting Team of The Law Times conducted a survey to evaluate law firm services, polling 588 legal professionals from 117 companies affiliated with 30 major conglomerates such as Samsung, SK, Hyundai Motor, and LG, as well as 5 major financial holding groups including Shinhan, Woori, Hana, and Nonghyup. This survey spanned one year, from April 2023 to April 2024. The evaluation targeted 1,519 law firms registered with the Ministry of Justice.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The survey consisted of two parts: competency evaluation, which included 14 items such as Skill and Expertise, Performance Satisfaction, Willingness to Reappointment, and Adequacy of Fees; and evaluation of works in 11 fields, including Financial Securities, Mergers and Acquisitions, and Material Accidents. Respondents were asked to assign scores for each question on a scale of 5 (Strongly Agree), 4 (Agree), 3 (Moderate), 2 (Disagree), and 1 (Strongly Disagree). Additionally, respondents were asked to provide subjective feedback about which law firms or lawyers they considered the best and which ones did not meet expectations, along with reasons for their assessments.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;To ensure fairness in evaluation based on the sample size, six major law firms (Kim &amp; Chang, Lee &amp; Ko, Bae, Kim &amp; Lee, Yulchon, Shin &amp; Kim, and Yoon &amp; Yang) that received responses from 100 people or more were classified as 《Group 1》. Additionally, ten law firms that received responses from less than 100 individuals but had evaluations from at least 3 companies and 5 people or more were classified as 《Group 2》 for comparison. The remaining law firms were categorized as 《Group 3》.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;In 《Group 1》, Kim &amp; Chang received the highest score (4.54) in terms of 'Skill and Expertise.' However, they had the lowest evaluation (3.12) among all 23 law firms in Group 1, Group 2, and Group 3 in the category of 'Adequacy of Fees.'&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;In Performance Satisfaction, the law firms Shin &amp; Kim (4.35), Bae, Kim &amp; Lee (4.31), and Kim &amp; Chang (4.29) received high scores. For the category of Whether You Are Willing to Entrust a Case Again or Recommend It to Other Clients (Willingness of Reappointment and Recommendation), Shin &amp; Kim (4.41), Bae, Kim &amp; Lee (4.37), and Lee &amp; Ko (4.20) were ranked in order."&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;In addition, out of a total of 14 competency evaluations, including Substantial involvement of the partner in charge, Detailed and objective explanations (post-management), Procedural stability (whether or not to change lawyers), and Evaluation of public service activities, Shin &amp; Kim received the highest score in 10 fields. Kim &amp; Chang and Bae, Kim &amp; Lee secured first place scores in each of the remaining two categories. Regarding the background of Shin &amp; Kim's relatively high score, a Shin &amp; Kim official stated, 'In recent years, management reforms have led to active internal communication and persuasion. Competition among members has been strengthened by large-scale recruitment of talent, which seems to have led to good services for clients.'&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;In 《Group 2》, LIN received the highest score in 13 out of 14 item-specific competency evaluations. LIN ranked No. 1 in 10 fields, making it the “hidden champion” of the survey.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Compared to large law firms, the relatively smaller law firms in 《Group 2》 received an average score of 4.34 in the question 'Do they charge excessive or unreasonable fees?' This resulted in a favorable evaluation, considering it was higher than the average score of 3.87 for large law firms in 《Group 1》. Additionally, the evaluation of 《Group 2》 law firms in terms of organizational culture, such as teamwork and public interest activities, was relatively positive. In 《Group 2》, apart from LIN, HwaHyun, and Chang-chun also received favorable evaluations. Dongin stood out by ranking first in the category of actual business involvement of its partners, reflecting the firm's emphasis on the independence of individual partners. Furthermore, LKB &amp; Partners was noted for being "strong in litigation." These findings shed light on the diverse characteristics and strengths of law firms within 《Group 2》."&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;In terms of the number of respondents to the best law firm and the law firm that did not meet expectations, Kim &amp; Chang had the highest number of respondents with 123 and 25, respectively.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;In selecting the best lawyers by individual, Kim Sang-min, a labor expert in Bae, Kim &amp; Lee, was rated as the 'best lawyer' by 10 corporate legal professionals, followed by Oh Tae-hwan, a human resources and labor expert at Yoon &amp; Yang (6 people).&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;"The 'less-than-expected lawyers' comprised six from Kim &amp; Chang, five each from Lee &amp; Ko and Yulchon, four from Yoon &amp; Yang, and two each from Bae, Kim &amp; Lee and Shin &amp; Kim.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;In a total of 132 short-answer (optional) responses citing 'law firms and lawyers who did not meet expectations,' many direct comments were provided. These included remarks such as 'slow responses and delayed deployment of alternative partners,' 'negligence in handling cases when the assigned partners retired,' 'inappropriate behavior in accepting cases,' and 'fluctuating skills and provision of clumsy, principled opinions that did not align with corporate needs.'"&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Law firm evaluation in graphic form&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Below is a graphic that shows consumer evaluations of law firms belonging to 《Group 1》 at a glance. The graphic at the top is a graph that shows client ratings for five major items out of 14 competency evaluation items, including 'Skill and expertise' and 'Adequacy of fees'. Below that is a visualization of the evaluation of items in 11 fields, including 'IT·TMT' and 'Personal Information Protection'.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://image.lawtimes.co.kr/images/197907_9(1).jpg" alt="197907_9.jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://image.lawtimes.co.kr/images/shinkim(1)(1).jpg" alt="shinkim(1).jpg" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
